cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "clojure-llm: Can an 8B Model Beat Frontier Models at Clojure Code Generation?"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: nibzard
repository-code: "https://github.com/nibzard/clojure-llm"
url: "https://github.com/nibzard/clojure-llm"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-21"
abstract: >
  Training Qwen3 models with SFT and verifier-in-the-loop RLVR for Clojure
  code generation. A Qwen3-8B model with a verifier loop (best-of-8: 67.6%)
  exceeds GPT-5.4 single-pass (64.0%) on 111 held-out MultiPL-E Clojure
  tasks. Qwen3-30B SFT achieves 52.3% pass@1, beating Opus 4.7 (45.0%)
  by 7.3 percentage points. Best-of-16 ceiling reaches 83.8% (93/111 tasks).
keywords:
  - clojure
  - code-generation
  - reinforcement-learning
  - rlvr
  - sft
  - large-language-models
  - verification
  - multipl-e
